LENGTH: 1252 words
DATELINE: NEW YORK (CNN)


NEW YORK (CNN) -- two Protests swelled in cities nation-wide Friday, as police forces around the united states of america struggled to either corral or get rid of demonstrators from downtown parks and plazas in the ultra-modern development of the month-long "Occupy Wall Street" movement.
Dozens have been arrested in Denver, San Diego and New York, whilst similar demonstrations have been scheduled to take location in Washington, Orlando, Atlanta and Detroit. CNN iReporters sent in photos and video from "occupy" protests throughout several American cities.
In San Diego, CNN affiliate KFMB broadcast snap shots of police detaining demonstrators as they gathered amid tents and tarps strewn about a downtown plaza.
Protesters appeared to refuse to leave the area, sitting in columns atop the tarps and yelling, "Stay down" as police tried to put off them from the scene.
In Denver, authorities say 24 humans have been arrested as CNN affiliate KMGH broadcast aerial video of police detaining protesters in a downtown area of the city.
Colorado State Police patrol spokesman Mike Baker stated the demonstration could be damaged down into two awesome groups: The first was a part of what he described as the unique "Occupy" group, which maintained close conversation with regulation enforcement. The second, he said, was once a greater "radical" faction.
"These were the ones (police) got here into bother with today," Baker said.
Most in Denver have been charged for illegal behavior on nation property, he added, while one different man or woman used to be charged for simple assault. Another protester was once arrested for impeding traffic.
In New York , Police Department Deputy Commissioner Paul Browne stated police had arrested 14 demonstrators, after they sat down in roadways and blocked traffic, overturned trash bins, knocked over a police scooter and hurled bottles.
Wesleyan University pupil Ben Doernberg, who attended Friday's protest in Manhattan's economic district, shot video of at least one other demonstrator being hauled to the floor by using police.
The video captures a police officer pressing his night time stick against the lower back of the protester's neck in the course of the arrest, whilst the man is seen faced down on the pavement.
